    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but if it's just a way to manage crises instead of actually solving the root causes of war, isn't its \"success\" kind of an illusion? it seems like the whole institution is just a way for powerful countries to maintain the status quo through diplomacy rather than actually dealing with real issues like sovereignty or aggression. do historians see that as a feature or a bug?",
