      "content": "Historians widely recognize that the UN is fundamentally a tool of the powerful, which is a critical feature, not a bug, of its design. It is inherently constrained by the sovereign interests of its most powerful members, meaning it will always prioritize maintaining the existing global power structure. Therefore, its \"success\" is often defined by its ability to prevent the powerful from directly challenging the status quo, rather than achieving true global justice.",
